    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-28T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="386"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 659.119/195a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GSU1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-28T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 28, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>697. Referring your 1850, January 23, 2 p.m., following delivered today by War
                    Trade Board to Danish Minister, Washington: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>It seems wise, in order to avoid the possibility of future
                            misunderstanding, to say to Your Excellency that, in case our countries
                            are fortunate enough to reach an agreement, the conditions in our letter
                            of January 16 [<hi rend="italic">17</hi>], respecting Denmark’s export
                            to the Central Powers of butter, bacon, fish, cattle, and horses will be
                            held by us to apply as of and from the date of our said letter.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
